Body Parts: =====================================
Head: -------------------------------------------
Face: Front part of head
Forehead, Eyebrow, Eyelash, Eye, Nose, Lip, Teeth, Ear, Tongue
Cheek, Chin, Gums
Bridge of the nose, Nostril (nostrils)
Pupil (small round black hole in the center of eye) check pronunciation, 
Cornea (?)
Note: Pupil also refers to a child student at primary school. 
Arm and Leg: ------------------------------------
Arm, Forearm, Hand
Leg, Thigh, Calf, Foot
Hand and Foot: ----------------------------------
Hand (Hands)
Finger (Fingers): We have only 4 fingers in a hand. Thumb is not a finger.
Thumb: short thick part on the side of your hand next to your four fingers.
Thumb, Index finger, Middle finger, Ring finger, Little finger
Fingernail, Thumbnail
Foot (feet)
Toe (Toes): 5 movable parts at the end of each foot.
Big Toe, Little Toe, Heel, Instep, Arch
Toe nail
Torso: ------------------------------------------
Torso: Your torso is the main part of your body, and does not include your head, arms, and legs.
Stomach: (where food is digested) check pronunciation
A fat (big) stomach (not fat abdomen)
Intestine: (from where food passes after it has left your stomach) check pronunciation
Abdomen: part below chest containing stomach and intestine
Abdominals (Abs): Muscels in the abdomen.
Navel, Shoulder. 
Spine: row of bones down your back.
Spinal Cord: thick cord of nerves inside your spine which connect your brain to nerves in all parts of your body.
Shoulder Blades: are the two large, flat, triangular bones that you have in the upper part of your back, below your shoulders.
Joints: -----------------------------------------
Knee: Ghutna
Ankle: takhna
Elbow: Kuuni
Wrist: Kalai
Teeth: ------------------------------------------
Tooth (Teeth): any one of incisor, canine or molar.
Incisor: one the sharp teeth at the front of mouth which cut food when you bite into it. (check pronunciation)
Canine: one of the four pointed teeth in the human mouth.
Molar: one of the large teeth at the back of the mouth for crushing and chewing.
Type of Hairs: ----------------------------------
Straight, Spiky, Skinhead, Wavy, Curly, Crew Cut, Cornrow
Ponytail, Plait (Braid) (check pronunciation)
Other Parts: ------------------------------------
Neck
Buttock/Bottom: two rounded fleshy parts of your body that you sit on.
Waist: kamar
Hip (Hips): an area below the waist and above the legs at either side of the body
Crotch (Groins): part of the body between the tops of your legs.
(Glover kicked him hard in the crotch.)
Disease: ========================================
Sick (Ill): not well or healthy (physically or mentally ill).
Homesick: unhappy because of being away from home for a long period.
Lovesick: sad because the person you love does not love you.
Blister: A blister is a painful swelling on the surface of your skin. Blisters contain a clear liquid and are usually caused by heat or by something repeatedly rubbing your skin.
Hay Fever: If someone is suffereing from hay fever, they sneeze and their eyes itch, because they are allergic to grass or flowers.
Sneeze, headache, toothache, cold, acne, 



How are you today?-----------------------------
I'm very well, thanks.
I'm fine, thanks.
I don't fell very well today. (I'll probably be OK tomorrow).
I feel ill. (Perhaps a serious problem.)
That fish was bad. I think I'm going to be sick! (I want to vomit.)
I've got headache.
I've got a cold.
